Brains are fucking weird. Small monkeys with brains the size of a peach pit are about as smart as toddlers. Whales with brains the size of you don't seem to be any more intelligent than any other large mammal.

There definitely seems to be some scalar issue with body size, like a certain density of neural activity is required to facilitate all the sensory and muscular information. All cells are the same size essentially so a whale has a massive ammount more muscular and sensory nerves than a monkey and that appears to simply just require more brain to make it work.

Humans are exceptional because of the proportion of our brain size to body ratio, and even that isn't exactly true because there was that one french guy who had lost like 70% of his brain matter due to a rare medical condition and yet seemed to be a normal guy of slightly below average intelligence because the neural tissue he did have was continuously remapping itself as the condition progressed.

So yeah, brains are fucking weird.

Anonymous Thu 09 Jun 2022 07:59:18 No.48383797 Report
Quoted By:
>>48380923
The brain is plastic. Obviously it's hard to judge the impact on potential intelligence, but there are people walking around with literally half a brain. If that happens to an adult, you are at the very least losing control over half your body and facing some serious cognitive and personality changes. Of course, the fact that you can survive it at all is already miraculous in its own right. But if it happens young enough the brain adapts, and the individual adapts to missing half the brain. This is why this happens not through accidents, but through epilepsy treatment.

You see something similar with the elderly. In some people the brain will atrophy over age, developing large areas of fluid space. Yet these elderly are perfectly normal.
